%Tutorial --------------------------  EDIT  ---------------------------
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
+
%                     -----------------------------------
                      ×      Edit Macro  "EDMODE"       ×
                      -----------------------------------
+
%HEX :+
   Use%HEX+to turn HEX mode on or off ("ON" is the default) and to indic
   whether you want the display to be in vertical (VERT) or data (DATA)
   (VERT is the default).
   When HEX mode is on, the cursor will be positioned to the hexadecimal
   representation of the data after a successfull FIND command.
   When HEX mode is on, the columns line(s) are specially formatted to m
   easier to find the hexadecimal representation of a specific column.

   More topic will be presented in the EDIT tutorial.
+
+Enter%&EPF+to exit the tutorial and return to the EDIT modes control pa
+Hit%ENTER+to go on to the next tutorial panel
)INIT
  &EPF = PFK(END)
  IF (&EPF = &Z)
    &EPF = 'END'
  &D = TRUNC(&EPF,2)
  &DT = .TRAIL
  &D = TRUNC(&DT,1)
  IF (&D = '0')
    &DT = .TRAIL
    &EPF = 'PF&DT'
)PROC
)END
